Machine Learning Engineer Job Description
**Job Title: Machine Learning Software Engineer** **Company: Tech Innovators Inc.** **Location: San Francisco, CA** **Job Type: Full-time** **Salary: $130,000 - $150,000 per year** **About Us:** Tech Innovators Inc. is a cutting-edge technology company based in San Francisco, CA. We specialize in developing innovative solutions using machine learning and artificial intelligence. Our team is passionate about creating products that make a real impact, and we're looking for a talented Machine Learning Software Engineer to join our crew. **Job Description:** We're seeking an experienced Machine Learning Software Engineer to design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks. As a key member of our engineering team, you will work on developing predictive models, natural language processing, and computer vision applications. Your expertise will help us drive business growth, improve product quality, and stay ahead of the competition. **Key Responsibilities:** * Design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business problems and develop solutions using machine learning * Develop and maintain large-scale machine learning systems, including data pipelines and model deployment * Work with large datasets to train and optimize machine learning models * Stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in machine learning and deep learning * Participate in code reviews and contribute to the improvement of the overall code quality * Collaborate with data scientists to develop and implement data-driven solutions **Requirements:** * Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field * 3+ years of experience in software development with a focus on machine learning * Expertise in Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks * Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals, including supervised and unsupervised learning, regression, classification, and clustering * Experience with deep learning frameworks, such as TensorFlow, Keras, or PyTorch * Strong programming skills in Python, with experience in software development and testing * Experience with data structures, algorithms, and software design patterns * Excellent problem-solving skills, with the ability to analyze complex problems and develop creative solutions * Strong communication and teamwork skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams **Nice to Have:** * Experience with cloud-based machine learning platforms, such as Google Cloud AI Platform or Amazon SageMaker * Familiarity with agile development methodologies and version control systems, such as Git * Experience with containerization using Docker and Kubernetes * Knowledge of data visualization tools, such as Matplotlib, Seaborn, or Plotly * Experience with big data technologies, such as Hadoop, Spark, or NoSQL databases **What We Offer:** * Competitive salary: $130,000 - $150,000 per year * Comprehensive benefits package, including medical, dental, and vision insurance * 401(k) matching program * Generous paid time off and holidays * Opportunities for professional growth and development * Collaborative and dynamic work environment * Access to cutting-edge technologies and tools * Recognition and rewards for outstanding performance **How to Apply:** If you're passionate about machine learning and software development, and you're looking for a challenging and rewarding role, please submit your resume and a cover letter explaining why you're the perfect fit for this position. We can't wait to hear from you!
What is the primary job responsibility of the Machine Learning Software Engineer at Tech Innovators Inc.?
qa
The primary job responsibility is to design, develop, and deploy machine learning models.

**Job Title: Machine Learning Software Engineer** **Company: Tech Innovators Inc.** **Location: San Francisco, CA** **Job Type: Full-time** **Salary: $130,000 - $150,000 per year** **About Us:** Tech Innovators Inc. is a cutting-edge technology company based in San Francisco, CA. We specialize in developing innovative solutions using machine learning and artificial intelligence. Our team is passionate about creating products that make a real impact, and we're looking for a talented Machine Learning Software Engineer to join our crew. **Job Description:** We're seeking an experienced Machine Learning Software Engineer to design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks. As a key member of our engineering team, you will work on developing predictive models, natural language processing, and computer vision applications. Your expertise will help us drive business growth, improve product quality, and stay ahead of the competition. **Key Responsibilities:** * Design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business problems and develop solutions using machine learning * Develop and maintain large-scale machine learning systems, including data pipelines and model deployment * Work with large datasets to train and optimize machine learning models * Stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in machine learning and deep learning * Participate in code reviews and contribute to the improvement of the overall code quality * Collaborate with data scientists to develop and implement data-driven solutions **Requirements:** * Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field * 3+ years of experience in software development with a focus on machine learning * Expertise in Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks * Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals, including supervised and unsupervised learning, regression, classification, and clustering * Experience with deep learning frameworks, such as TensorFlow, Keras, or PyTorch * Strong programming skills in Python, with experience in software development and testing * Experience with data structures, algorithms, and software design patterns * Excellent problem-solving skills, with the ability to analyze complex problems and develop creative solutions * Strong communication and teamwork skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams **Nice to Have:** * Experience with cloud-based machine learning platforms, such as Google Cloud AI Platform or Amazon SageMaker * Familiarity with agile development methodologies and version control systems, such as Git * Experience with containerization using Docker and Kubernetes * Knowledge of data visualization tools, such as Matplotlib, Seaborn, or Plotly * Experience with big data technologies, such as Hadoop, Spark, or NoSQL databases **What We Offer:** * Competitive salary: $130,000 - $150,000 per year * Comprehensive benefits package, including medical, dental, and vision insurance * 401(k) matching program * Generous paid time off and holidays * Opportunities for professional growth and development * Collaborative and dynamic work environment * Access to cutting-edge technologies and tools * Recognition and rewards for outstanding performance **How to Apply:** If you're passionate about machine learning and software development, and you're looking for a challenging and rewarding role, please submit your resume and a cover letter explaining why you're the perfect fit for this position. We can't wait to hear from you!
Explain the key responsibilities and requirements
summarization
Key Responsibilities: As a Machine Learning Software Engineer at Tech Innovators Inc., the key responsibilities include designing, developing, and deploying machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks. The role involves collaborating with cross-functional teams to identify business problems and develop solutions using machine learning. Additionally, the engineer will develop and maintain large-scale machine learning systems, work with large datasets to train and optimize machine learning models, and stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in machine learning and deep learning. The role also requires participating in code reviews, contributing to the improvement of the overall code quality, and collaborating with data scientists to develop and implement data-driven solutions. Requirements: To be eligible for the Machine Learning Software Engineer role, candidates must have a Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field. They must also have at least 3 years of experience in software development with a focus on machine learning. Expertise in Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks is required, along with a strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals. The ideal candidate will have experience with deep learning frameworks, strong programming skills in Python, and experience with data structures, algorithms, and software design patterns. Excellent problem-solving skills, strong communication and teamwork skills, and the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams are also essential.

We specialize in developing innovative solutions using machine learning and artificial intelligence. Our team is passionate about creating products that make a real impact, and we're looking for a talented Machine Learning Software Engineer to join our crew. **Job Description:** We're seeking an experienced Machine Learning Software Engineer to design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks. As a key member of our engineering team, you will work on developing predictive models, natural language processing, and computer vision applications. Your expertise will help us drive business growth, improve product quality, and stay ahead of the competition. **Key Responsibilities:** * Design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business problems and develop solutions using machine learning * Develop and maintain large-scale machine learning systems, including data pipelines and model deployment * Work with large datasets to train and optimize machine learning models * Stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in machine learning and deep learning * Participate in code reviews and contribute to the improvement of the overall code quality * Collaborate with data scientists to develop and implement data-driven solutions **Requirements:** * Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field * 3+ years of experience in software development with a focus on machine learning * Expertise in Python, TensorFlow, and neural networks * Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals, including supervised and unsupervised learning, regression, classification, and clustering * Experience with deep learning frameworks, such as TensorFlow, Keras, or PyTorch * Strong programming skills in Python, with experience in software development and testing * Experience with data structures, algorithms, and software design patterns * Excellent problem-solving skills, with the ability to analyze complex problems and develop creative solutions * Strong communication and teamwork skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams **Nice to Have:** * Experience with cloud-based machine learning platforms, such as Google Cloud AI Platform or Amazon SageMaker * Familiarity with agile development methodologies and version control systems, such as Git * Experience with containerization using Docker and Kubernetes * Knowledge of data visualization tools, such as Matplotlib, Seaborn, or Plotly * Experience with big data technologies, such as Hadoop, Spark, or NoSQL databases **What We Offer:** * Competitive salary: $130,000 - $150,000 per year * Comprehensive benefits package, including medical, dental, and vision insurance * 401(k) matching program * Generous paid time off and holidays * Opportunities for professional growth and development * Collaborative and dynamic work environment * Access to cutting-edge technologies and tools * Recognition and rewards for outstanding performance **How to Apply:** If you're passionate about machine learning and software development, and you're looking for a challenging and rewarding role, please submit your resume and a cover letter explaining why you're the perfect fit for this position. We can't wait to hear from you!

          Teapot SynthQA

          This is a synthetic dataset created to fine-tune small language models such as Teapot LLM.

          Dataset

          This dataset consists of synthetic articles and questions generated by DeepSeek-V3. Questions cover a variety of tasks and were manually annotated to ensure high quality responses due to the size of the dataset. The data was specifically designed to represent various common language tasks and to utilize open source models to ensure permissive licensing for fine-tuned models.

          Tasks

          • Question Answering (qa) Conversational answers to questions based on context
          • True/False (boolean) Questions that can be answered using true/false statements
          • Extraction (extraction) Questions that request short answers in specific formats
          • JSON (json) Questions designed to train models to extract relevant json from queries
          • Hallucintation Proofing (unanswerable) Questions that can not be answered from the context used to condition the model to avoid hallucinations

          Uses

          This dataset can be used to fine-tune models to achieve better performance across various languages tasks, even for small models.

          License

          This dataset is licensed under the MIT License
